1. RESOLVED — Restock management numeric inputs now accept real-number decimal entry through true numeric controls.

Root cause of failed prior attempt
- The prior fix kept fields as controlled `type="text"` inputs and parsed keystrokes immediately into numbers.
- In React controlled inputs, this collapses transient-but-valid typing states (for example `.` or `12.`) back to numeric values (`NaN` or `12`), which makes the decimal point appear "rejected" while typing.
- So even with `inputMode="decimal"` and decimal regex patterns, users could still experience blocked/stripped dot entry depending on typing sequence.

What was truly fixed
- Converted affected restock numeric fields from text+pattern controls to real numeric controls:
  - `type="number"`
  - `step="any"` (decimal-capable)
- Kept existing `parseFloat(...)` handling for persistence and calculations.
- This removes dependency on text-pattern matching for decimal acceptance and allows browser-native real-number entry behavior for decimal values.

Price-field coverage (explicit)
- Supplier product editor "Unit Cost" uses numeric decimal input.
- Supplier creation/edit "Minimum Order Amount" uses numeric decimal input.
- Inventory item-to-supplier "Supplier Unit Price" uses numeric decimal input (including default and per-supplier override flows).
- Purchase-order flows use numeric decimal input for unit cost and quantity fields in manual PO and edit/receive flows.

Where this was applied
- `components/admin/restock/new-restock-request-form.tsx`
- `components/admin/restock/suppliers-list.tsx`
- `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx`

How to verify truthful resolution
1) Start the app and navigate to Admin → Restock flows.
2) In updated numeric fields, type `12.50`, `0.99`, `.75`, and `103.275`.
3) Confirm:
   - Decimal points are accepted during typing.
   - Decimal values remain editable and persist after blur/focus cycles.
   - Save/update flows retain decimals and render expected currency display.

Command-line verification performed
- Verified impacted restock forms now use `type="number"` + `step="any"` for decimal-capable numeric entry.
